w.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                      | <li> Teach the patient about his medical condition and the related care and management.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                      | <li> Coordinate patient care by communicating effectively and frequently with the other members of the team involved in the patient's care.    .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                h4.text-dark YOUR ROLE IN INFECTION CONTROL            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Practice good hand washing before and after all patient contract.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Use universal precautions for all patients.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Instruct patients and caregivers in the infection control measures that are necessary for each individual case (i.e.., immunosuppresses, IV wound care) and document.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Handle sharps with extreme care. Do not bend, recap or manipulate in any way.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Double bag, close securely and dispose in the trash any waste soiled with blood fluids.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Place sharps only in a sharps container or a container of impervious plastic which can be closed.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Keep your hands away from your mouth nose and eyes as much as possible and especially during patient care.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | <li> Be carefull to keep your skin, especially the skin on you hands intact and healthy.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | <li> Report any needle stick or mucuos membrane exposure to blood or body fluids immediately to your supervisor.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | <li> All members of the team (nurses,aides,homemakers) should be alerted to the signs and symptoms of infection and report them to the case manager or MD as appropriate.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | <li> Monitor those patients susceptible to infection (Wounds, foley IV immunosuppressed) for signs and symptoms such as fever, swelling or drainage.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | <li> For the patient or caregiver who has been taught a procedure, periodically re-evalucate their technique to assure it is still adequate.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | <li> Use good technique with all sterille procedures.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | <li> Be certain patients and caregivers are independent and use good technique before having them do procedures on their own.    .form-row.col-lg-12      .form-group.col-md-6          label.text-dark Employee / Contractor :          input.form-control.waves-float(type='text' value='' name='pg12employeecontractor')      .form-group.col-md-6          label.text-dark Date :          .input-group              input.form-control(type='date', placeholder='mm/dd/yyyy' value='' name='pg12dateoforientation')              .input-group-append                 span.input-group-text                      i.mdi.mdi-calendar